==English==
===Etymology===
Cat + [[waul]], wawl, to [[cry]] as a [[cat]].

===Pronunciation===
Cat"er*waul 
*{{audio|en-us-caterwaul.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|caterwaul||}}
#''(intransitive)'' To [[cry]] as cats in [[rutting]] time; to make a [[harsh]], [[offensive]] noise.
# to have a noisy argument

